The shortest version of my process I can make for you. Here’s the real timeline:
1. Make all the molds - days to weeks
2. Make the form - 5 min 
3. Plan the design - 15 min
4. Make and attach all the sprigs - 18 hours
5. Carve in the details - 4 hours
6. Dry - a few weeks
7. Fire - 17 hours plus a day to cool
8. Glaze - 3 days
9. Fire again - 18 hours plus a few days to cool 
10. Fire on lusters - a day 
It’s a lesson in patience! #pottery #ceramics #sculpture #taniagoldberg #clay

Another sneak peek into my process. I often wash the underglaze off under running water to get the cleanest wash and hence the most contrast between the white highs and the black lows. This of course thoroughly waterlogs my pieces, and therefore makes them susceptible to kiln explosions. To avoid any issues, I often dry them for several days before continuing the glazing process. #pottery #ceramicart #sculpture #fineart #clay

The good, the bad, and the ugly. Send tequila. I broke my 6 year streak of no cracks today, guys. Out of 5 mermaid mugs that I made as a special gift for my subscribers… 3 cracked in the firing. I am pretty sure it’s the crazy heat and humidity fluctuations affecting the drying… but of course it could also be just this batch of clay. What can I say, except that I have to remake them and hope it was a fluke. Same clay, same firing schedule, same everything else, for the past 6 years. Be a potter, they said! Lol! (On the bright side, everything else fired fine). I am thinking to kintsugi them and offer them for $25 as pretty pencil holders, what do you think? Any takers? 
#pottery #potteryfail #ceramics #mug #clay #kilnfolk

STUDIO UPDATE. In case if you’re wondering… I did NOT fall off the face of the earth (not for the lack of trying). My clay body is suddenly bipolar and identifies as the Kit Kat bar whenever it feels like it. 🆘 Now, I’ve been using it almost exclusively for about 8 years and have not made any changes in my process, so call me crazy but I highly suspect that the clay formula itself has been changed due to the known raw material shortages in the country. SO. No crying over spilled milk in my studio. I am changing a few things for my drying process, and slowing down my firing a little more. I will also be talking to the manufacturer to see if they have any suggestions. 📝 IN THE MEANTIME. I will be making a lot of different mugs. Some commissions, but most will be mugs that don’t take a week to sculpt. I need to make hundreds of them to see if my changes are making a statistical difference. As soon as I have the process streamlined again, I will dive right back into my more complicated custom work, I promise. The silver lining is that you guys will be able to purchase a lot of new mugs in my Etsy soon (the ones that came out perfect). The not-so-silver lining is that my commissions now resemble the Lazy River at Blizzard Beach on the 4th of July 🐌🐌🐌 I will continue to work on them whenever I can though, remaking them as many times as it takes, as I work to solve this weirdness. Best case scenario, it was just a bad batch of clay. Time will tell. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PATIENCE! I will keep you updated! 🙏🏼💖 #pottery #fineart #ceramics #potterystudio #clay

One of my current projects. A little raised relief like this can take a day to make. First, I have to study the image, figure out my layers, figure out which ones will be built up and which ones carved in, learn and draw each individual layer, superimpose them onto the drawing, blend and add detail, carve in the deep layers, then go back and fix anything that looks “off”. Of course, this one is a character from a video game, so there’s no mold to make because it has to be a one-of-a-kind piece due to the copyright laws. I can literally never make it again… but sometimes I just can’t say no to a challenge, especially in the fantasy/sci-fi genre that I was a huge fan of growing up! #masterchief #masterchiefcollection #halo #pottery #sculpture

Not ok. After talking to some of my more experienced colleagues (thank you, Steven Drollinger!) we have come to the conclusion that one of the relays went bad in the kiln during the firing. It is taking too long to cool down, and I don’t know what it will do to everything inside. I have it completely unplugged and the lid cracked a hair at this point… but this could be a very serious failure requiring kiln repairs and remakes. Do ceramics, they said 🤦🏻‍♀️😣 Excuse me while I go find some tequila. @claykingceramics do you deliver kilns to South Florida? I might just get a bigger one. #pottery #ceramics #clay #potterystudio #potteryfail

Sometimes you just get lucky. I hit a cone hotter than I wanted to. It was definitely a stuck relay, I can hear it buzz violently as soon as I plug in the kiln. BUT. The mugs and platters are fine, thank G-d! No issues whatsoever. That said, I am going to STOP pushing the envelope and send your commissions to their respective homes now (before I do something stupid again). I will be in touch with everyone whose work was in this load. There will be a few dishes and mugs going into my Etsy today. I am trying to decide if I want to upgrade to a new kiln in the meantime. I would love to have the WiFi capability so I can remotely monitor my firings, but it’s a $3000 upgrade. What is that, like a month worth of groceries nowadays?! Decisions, decisions. Have a great weekend, everyone! Thank you for all of your support, as always! #pottery #ceramics #sculpture #clay #kiln
